12 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
13 An Act relating to 2-1-1 services; creating the 2-1-1
Hotline Revolving Fund; specifying type of fund and
14 source of monies; stating purpose of the fund;
providing for expenditure of monies; providing for
15 codification; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
16
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3022 of Title 56, unless there
22 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
24 fund for the Department of Human Services to be designated the “2-1-
SB1290 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 1 Ho tline Revolving Fund”. The fund shall be a continuing fund, not
2 subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of all monies
3 received by the Department from legislative appropriations provided
4 for the purpose of maintaining a robust 2-1-1 system in this state.
5 All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
6 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Department for
7 the purpose provided for in this section. Expenditures from the
8 fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
9 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
10 Office of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
11 payment.
12 B. No monies from the 2-1-1 Hotline Revolving Fund shall be
13 used to provide referrals, information, or assistance to any
14 organization, entity, or service that performs, promotes, or
15 facilitates abortions. Instead, the 2-1-1 system shall prioritize
16 referrals to crisis pregnancy centers, adoption agencies, and other
17 life-affirming resources that support expectant mothers and families
18 in choosing life. The Department of Human Services shall ensure
19 compliance with this subsection through annual audits and reporting
20 to the Legislature.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
22 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
23 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
24
